            "id": 74258,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>¿Qué sucede cuando usamos <code>i &gt; 0</code> en la condición?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"for\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" (\" /><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" i = \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"; i &gt; \" /><text value=\"0\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"; i--) {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(i);\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"5\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"4\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"3\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"2\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"1\" /></content></output></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">El bucle continúa mientras <code>i</code> sea mayor que <code>0</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">El bucle no funciona</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">El bucle continúa mientras <code>i</code> sea mayor que <code>0</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
